		<mj-section padding-bottom="0">
			<mj-column width="560px">
				<mj-text>
					Dear colleague,<br />
					<br />
					The previous newsletters have already provided more
					information on the purple (SBTi) and orange (Certified
					Sourcing) pillars of our strategy. In this newsletter, we
					would like to shine a spotlight on the blue pillar (Acting
					Responsible) and introduce Jonny Young, who will be taking
					the lead on this topic. To wrap up, we’re sharing a sneak
					peek from the red pillar. Madelon (Group HR Manager)
					introduces “Boost Yourself”, a wellbeing-focused initiative
					designed to support our people.<br />
					<br />
					As you have heard, I will be leaving DFG after 13.5
					wonderful years to continue my commitment to driving
					positive impact as an independent entrepreneur. I’m proud of
					the trust I received six years ago to start building DFG’s
					sustainability strategy from the ground up. What began as an
					idea has since evolved into a fully-fledged IMPACT2030
					strategy, supported by a strong internal sustainability team
					and a dedicated group of Sustainability Ambassadors across
					our companies. I’d like to take this opportunity to
					sincerely thank you all for the collaboration over the past
					years.
				</mj-text>
			</mj-column>
		</mj-section>
		<mj-section padding-top="0" padding-bottom="0">
